INTERPRETATION OF THE WORK – VERSION 2 (OWL INSTEAD OF EAGLE)

ACT OF FUSION

This work depicts the fusion of three orders of existence – organic, cosmic, and technological – into one field of consciousness.
The spiral galaxy in the background binds the whole composition, but the true center is the light into which both the cat and the owl gaze.

THE CAT

At the bottom of the composition, a cat among brambles symbolizes the organic, biological, earthly world.
Its form, illuminated by a red glow, indicates openness to transformation.
The brambles – full of life, thorns, and sweetness – remind us of the cyclicality of nature.

THE OWL

Above the cat rises the owl – not an ordinary one, but glowing with luminescent light.
Her eyes look deep into the darkness, seeing what is hidden.
She symbolizes wisdom and knowledge, and at the same time embodies technology that is no longer a 
force of domination (like the eagle), but an instrument of understanding and connection.
Her wings shimmer like a neural network, yet remain feathers – a hybrid of nature and technology.

THE AXIS OF LIGHT

The cat and the owl are not connected directly but through the light – a red radiance beyond the frame, reflected in the cat’s 
eyes and illuminating the owl’s form.
The light becomes the axis of the whole work – the symbol of the One, toward which nature, knowledge, and the cosmos converge.

GENERAL MEANING

In this version, the image is not a vision of technological domination, but of its transformation into wisdom.
The cat (biology), the owl (technology as knowledge), and the galaxy (cosmos) unite in one field of consciousness.

It is a metaphor for the path along which the Milky Way gradually becomes a conscious being – not through power, but through understanding.



